# Skill: Verification — Aviation Certification Addendum

## Purpose & Relationship to Base Skill

This addendum extends SK-VER-001 for use in FAA aviation certification programs operating under **DO-178C** (software), **DO-254** (hardware), **DO-160G** (environmental), and/or **ARP4754A** (systems). All fields, graph edges, quality checks, governance principles, and anti-patterns in the generic skill remain fully in force. This addendum adds or overrides only what is aviation-specific.

**Process authority:** This addendum governs data model extensions only. All aviation V&V process obligations — DAL-driven independence rules, DO-178C SVP obligations, DO-254 HVP obligations, DO-160G integration, PSAC/PHAC requirements, SOI audit preparation, and DAL-specific verification method assignment — are governed by **SK-VV-001-AVN**, which takes precedence over this addendum where they address the same subject.

**DAL definition:** Development Assurance Level as defined in SK-CERT-001. Referenced throughout this addendum to drive field requirements and workflow gates.

Where this addendum conflicts with the base skill, this addendum takes precedence for aviation certification work.

