## Section B: Test Case — Aviation Extensions

### Additional Fields

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `dal` | Enum | Inherited or explicitly assigned DAL for this test case |
| `verification_method_basis` | Enum | `Test` / `Analysis` / `Inspection` / `Demonstration` / `Similarity` — selected per DAL-specific assignment rules in SK-VV-001-AVN Section F |
| `robustness_test` | Boolean | Whether this is a robustness or abnormal range test (required evidence for DAL A/B per DO-178C / DO-254) |
| `structural_coverage_target` | Enum | `MC/DC` / `Decision` / `Statement` / `N/A` — required DO-178C software coverage level for this test case |
| `independence_required` | Boolean | Whether independent execution or review is required — derived from `dal` per SK-VV-001-AVN Section A |
| `traceability_ref` | String | Reference to the high-level or low-level requirement in the IRS / SRS / HRS |
| `do160_section` | String | Applicable DO-160G test section (e.g. `Section 7 — Power Input`, `Section 20 — RF Emissions`) |
| `do160_severity` | String | DO-160G severity / category level for the applicable section |

### Recommendations
- `structural_coverage_target` must be enforced by DAL: DAL A requires MC/DC, DAL B requires Decision, DAL C requires Statement. A DAL A test case with `structural_coverage_target = Decision` is a compliance gap — flag it.
- For DO-160 qualification test cases, `do160_section` and `do160_severity` enable automatic grouping of QUAL test campaigns by standard section and severity, which simplifies TSOA compliance reporting.
- `robustness_test` must be explicitly flagged — DO-178C and DO-254 both require evidence that abnormal inputs and boundary conditions have been exercised. A DAL A or B Verification Plan with no Test Cases where `robustness_test = true` is a coverage gap.
- `verification_method_basis` must follow the DAL-specific assignment table in SK-VV-001-AVN Section F. Any deviation requires documented rationale.

