## Section C: Test Run — Aviation Extensions

### Additional Fields

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `lab_accreditation` | String | Accreditation of the test lab (e.g. NADCAP, A2LA) — required for formal qualification test runs |
| `witness` | Reference | DER, ACO, or customer witness present during the run — required for key certification test events |
| `test_report_ref` | String | Formal test report document number — required before the Test Run can contribute to VCRM closure |
| `configuration_index` | String | Exact hardware / software / firmware configuration index under test — must be consistent with conformity inspection records per SK-INTF-002-AVN Section D |
| `deviation_notices` | List | Approved deviations or waivers active during the run |

### Recommendations
- `equipment_calibration_verified` (from the base skill) is a **hard workflow gate** in aviation programs — the Test Run must not be settable to `In Progress` unless this field is `true`. This is enforced more strictly than the base skill recommendation; treat it as a system-enforced constraint, not a data quality check. (Authority: SK-VV-001-AVN Section D.)
- `configuration_index` is distinct from `build_version` — it references the formal configuration management record and must be traceable to what was approved for test. Inconsistency between `configuration_index` and the conforming test article is a certification finding. Coordinate with SK-INTF-002-AVN Section D.
- `witness` should reference a structured Witness Record node if your model tracks DER authorizations and witness credentials as first-class artifacts — this enables formal witness record generation from the Test Run.

